private void PopulateAssignedCourseData(Instructor instructor)
{
    var allCourses = db.Courses;
    var instructorCourses = new HashSet<int>(instructor.CourseAssignments.Select(c => c.CourseID));


```

The method tries to select from CourseAssignments without checking if it's null first. In my test, I'm creating an instructor with just a HireDate, leaving CourseAssignments uninitialized. I need to initialize it as an empty collection in the test setup.

